news.title: Apple India renews three leases for office in Mumbai's Bandra-Kurla Complex
news.para: The company has renewed the leases through three agreements with landlord Agni Commex LLP for offices on the 6th, 7th and 8th floor of the tower. The rentals for the leases have been set between Rs 400 and Rs 402 per sq ft a month as against earlier rentals of Rs 374 per sq ft per month.

news.title: Chinese property magnate loses $1 billion in Evergrande panic
news.para: Zhang Yuanlin, chairman of Sinic Holdings Group, saw his net worth drop from $1.3 billion Monday morning to $250.7 million by the afternoon, according to Forbes, when his firm was forced to halt trading in Hong Kong following an 87 percent slump in its share price.

news.title: China Evergrande shares dive to 11-year low as default risks grow
news.para: Evergrande has been scrambling to raise funds to pay its many lenders, suppliers and investors, with regulators warning that its $305 billion of liabilities could spark broader risks to the country's financial system if not stabilised.

news.title: ICICI Home Finance to hire 600 people by December 2021
news.para: ​This recruitment drive across the country's branch network in sales and credit will enable the company to cater to the increasing demand in the affordable housing segment, it said in a release.

news.title: Buyer demand nudges up asking prices for UK houses: Survey
news.para: Real estate website Rightmove said asking prices rose by 0.3% in its September survey to reach a new record high of 338,462 pounds ($466,671), reversing a 0.3% drop in early August.

news.title: Kerala: Idukki collector says resort being constructed in landslide-prone area
news.para: The revenue department had earlier issued a memo to stop the construction of the Madapparampil resort at Pulippara near Pallivasal in Munnar after it was found that it was being constructed without obtaining the required approvals.

news.title: Hyderabad: 86 government buildings illegally built on GO 111 areas
news.para: These government structures include,“electricity offices, schools, Gram Panchayat buildings, Anganwadi centres, SHG building, police stations and other offices,” reads the document submitted to NGT that was hearing a case on GO 111 during that time.

news.title: Kolkata: Land hurdle hits New Garia-Airport metro work
news.para: Out of the total 20,180 square-metre land required for the station hub, 13,941sqm plot is yet to be acquired, causing massive time and cost overrun.

news.title: Scheme to map villages with drones fails to take off in Gujarat
news.para: ​​Information provided by the central government says that no drone flying has been undertaken in any of the villages of Gujarat so far and hence, no property cards have been issued under the new scheme to any farmer of the state.

news.title: Hyderabad: Illegal buildings overrun green zones under GO 111 due to lax enforcement
news.para: There is just one enforcement wing with 53 personnel for Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority (HMDA) which is spread over 7,200 sq km comprising seven districts, 70 mandals and 1,032 villages.

news.title: Buyers seek help from Badshapur MLA as builders violate norms
news.para: Highlighting their plight, the homebuyers complained that there is a widespread delay in completion of affordable housing projects with poor monitoring and enforcement by the concerned department.

news.title: China's Evergrande starts repaying investors with discounted properties
news.para: ​​Investors who opt for discounted real estate in lieu of cash can start contacting wealth managers for more details, Evergrande’s wealth division said in a post on its Wechat account.

news.title: Rising rents spark Berlin housing seizure referendum
news.para: Effective November 1, the increase of 12.34 euros ($14.54) on her monthly rent of 623.44 euros will be "difficult" to finance with her only income a disability pension, Lehmann tells AFP.

news.title: Chandigarh administration calls for revised draft policy on village development, lal dora
news.para: The decision was taken after a recent meeting with a representative of the Bengaluru-based consultant, which was chaired by UT adviser Dharam Pal.

news.title: HSVP to monetise unused land in Gurugram and Pataudi
news.para: Around 300 plots are expected to be developed on these land parcels and the HSVP is hoping to raise some Rs 500 crore from the auction of the same.
